title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1989-10-20
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Candyman, Picasso Moon, A Little Light, Tennessee Jed, Memphis Blues, Stagger Lee, Promised Land, California Earthquake

Set 2

Hey Pocky Way, Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Truckin'-> The Other One-> Drums-> Jam-> I Will Take You Home-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Thanks Waited a long time for this. Had an upfront dat done with AKG 414TL's that was a bit boomy, bassy. This is a joy to listen too and what an awesome second set. I loved every minute of this '89 Philly run not to mention the entire tour. Great work Hunter !
Cool show - good audio work! Smiling ear to ear at this one!  Great Atmosphere at this show - the Earthquake!  Then rockin' second set.  Had a poor copy of this for a long time - great re-work here!!

Last night? How can it be?....Have I been sleeping.... have I been dreaming? 23 long years gone by, Jerry dead and in the ground, Brent too....and yet it sounds like it happened last night, I feel like it happened last night. For those of you that miss them, like me, so much you could cry, you need to take some time off work, buy the biggest speakers you can buy, and blow the god damn windows outta the house with this one! 
I don't care for reviews that rate “The Best,”...after all that depends as much on the place the listener is at...as well as the band...when you hear it. That being said the 2nd set on this one is well....unbelievable!

Upgrade to board Best source IMO.  The boards are very sterile for this show.   Miller source is next best if you like a pure board.

I remember being disappointed with this show.  The band was distracted due to the earthquake, and you could feel the anxiety with them being so far away.  That said, it is testimony to the entire tour that this could be considered a weak show.  If you can get past the lyric flubs in Fire, the music is very nice.  Check out all the shows in this run even the ones with the set lists that do not stand out.  Very tight.  

3.5 rounded to 4.

Memphis Blues ? I'm liking this show, this is my first time hearing.  Started a little slow with Touch but it gets moving.

I thought my days of enjoying Memphis Blues were over but this one has some legs !

Great mix, thanks !!!!

Bay area Quake, Candlestick Park, World Series I remember this day & show well. Bay area Quake & Bay area teams & the Dead were in town. Candyman sticks out in my memory and the Scarlet>Fire. Danced with Lucy 1st & 3rd nite. Was beautiful. Loved every minute of it. Jerry playing Wolf, happy and healthy. Very good memories.
Hunter's Trix Thank you for aiding the sound of these "digital era" Healy SBDs.
